data.description: 3rd BEDROOM possibilities on the lower level. There is a full bath and room with a closet ready to be finished on the lower level to make this a true 3 bedroom home. Welcome to Seven Springs Lake Community! This home is nestled on the cul-de-sac with lake access from the cove as well as access from the main community location. This home boasts a true CHEF'S Kitchen with a double oven, 6 gas burner industrial stove, 2 sinks, island counter space with eating access, two garbage disposals, trash compactor (Wow! who has that these days??) and plenty of room to make your favorite culinary delights! All main rooms have a lake view! The living room features a stone hearth fireplace insert w/ plenty of built-in shelving for TV, books and photos of your loved ones. Real Hardwood floors throughout the main level. The lower level is ready to finish out w/ a mud room and a HUGE 2 car garage w/ plenty of extra room for storage. Small standing freezer in garage stays. If you have furry children, there is underground fencing in place. The seller will contribute up to $5000 in buyer closing costs and prepaids with an acceptable offer. $700 HOA fee each year. See attached docs for all community standards and regulations regarding lake and acreage usage. Septic was pumped in 2022. Natural Spring on property. ADT Security System available for new owner to use if they so choose. Buyer to verify taxes, exemptions, sq. footage, acreage & school system.
